Name: Emily Johnson
Age: 35
Gender: Female
Occupation: Teacher
Ethnicity: African American
Past Medical History: Asthma, allergies, and migraines

Emily Johnson is a 35-year-old teacher of African American descent who presents with a history of asthma, allergies, and migraines. She was recently diagnosed with systemic lupus erythematosus (SLE) after experiencing fatigue, joint pain, and a rash on her face. Emily has been experiencing symptoms for several months and has been managing her condition with medication and lifestyle changes. She is currently taking hydroxychloroquine and prednisone to manage her symptoms. Emily's medical team is working closely with her to manage her symptoms and prevent complications associated with SLE. Despite the challenges of living with a chronic illness, Emily remains optimistic and committed to managing her health.

Name: Sarah Johnson
Age: 28
Gender: Female
Occupation: Graphic Designer
Ethnicity: African-American
Past Medical History: Sarah was diagnosed with systemic lupus erythematosus (SLE) at the age of 24 following a series of unexplained symptoms such as joint pain, fatigue, and skin rashes. She also has a history of anxiety and depression, for which she receives regular therapy and medication. Sarah has been managing her lupus with a combination of medication, lifestyle changes, and regular check-ups with her rheumatologist. Despite occasional flare-ups, she remains optimistic about her health and continues to pursue her passion for design.

Name: Sarah Johnson
Age: 34
Gender: Female
Occupation: Marketing Manager
Ethnicity: African American
Past Medical History: Sarah was diagnosed with systemic lupus erythematosus (SLE) at the age of 30. She also has a history of migraines and occasional joint pain.

Sarah's SLE has been a challenge for her, as she experiences fatigue, joint pain, and skin rashes on a regular basis. Despite this, she manages to maintain her job as a marketing manager and is actively involved in her community. Sarah is a proud African American woman who advocates for lupus awareness and supports others with chronic illnesses.

Name: Sarah Johnson
Age: 32
Gender: Female
Occupation: Retail Sales Associate
Ethnicity: African American
Past Medical History: Asthma, Seasonal Allergies

Sarah Johnson is a 32-year-old African American woman who works as a retail sales associate. She was recently diagnosed with systemic lupus erythematosus (SLE), a chronic autoimmune disease that affects various parts of the body. Sarah's symptoms include joint pain, fatigue, and a rash on her face that worsens with sun exposure.

In addition to SLE, Sarah has a history of asthma and seasonal allergies. She has been prescribed medication to manage her symptoms and is under the care of a rheumatologist. Despite the challenges of living with a chronic illness, Sarah remains optimistic and focused on maintaining a healthy lifestyle. She enjoys spending time with her family and friends and participating in community events.
